fields.Name: Get Google Forms Responses
fields.Description: Retrieves responses from a Google Form with filtering, pagination, and search capabilities. Requires Google OAuth 2.0 authentication with forms.responses.readonly scope. Supports date ranges, completion status filters, and automatic pagination through all responses.

fields.Name: CompanyID
fields.Description: The Company Integration ID for Google Forms authentication

fields.Name: FormID
fields.Description: The Google Form ID (found in the form URL)

fields.Name: PageSize
fields.Description: Number of responses per page (1-1000, default 100)

fields.Name: PageToken
fields.Description: Token for pagination - get next page using this token from previous response

fields.Name: Filter
fields.Description: Filter expression for responses (e.g., 'timestamp > "2023-01-01T00:00:00Z"')

fields.Name: GetAllPages
fields.Description: If true, automatically fetch all pages of responses (up to MaxResponses)

fields.Name: MaxResponses
fields.Description: Maximum number of responses to retrieve when GetAllPages is true (default 10000)

fields.Name: Responses
fields.Description: Array of response objects with all answers, metadata, and submission details

fields.Name: TotalResponses
fields.Description: Total number of responses available for the form

fields.Name: Count
fields.Description: Number of responses returned in this request

fields.Name: NextPageToken
fields.Description: Token to use for retrieving the next page of responses

fields.Name: HasMore
fields.Description: Boolean indicating if more pages are available

fields.Name: Get Single Google Forms Response
fields.Description: Retrieves details of a specific Google Form response by its unique response ID. Requires Google OAuth 2.0 authentication with forms.responses.readonly scope. Includes all answers, metadata, and submission timestamps.

fields.Name: CompanyID
fields.Description: The Company Integration ID for Google Forms authentication

fields.Name: FormID
fields.Description: The Google Form ID

fields.Name: ResponseID
fields.Description: The unique response ID to retrieve

fields.Name: Response
fields.Description: Complete response object with all answers and metadata

fields.Name: SubmittedAt
fields.Description: Timestamp when response was submitted

fields.Name: LastSubmittedAt
fields.Description: Timestamp when response was last updated (if edited)

fields.Name: Answers
fields.Description: Object mapping question IDs to answer objects with values and text

fields.Name: RespondentEmail
fields.Description: Email address of respondent (if form collects email)

fields.Name: Get Google Forms Response Statistics
fields.Description: Calculates comprehensive statistics from Google Form responses including completion rates, response trends, popular answers, and time-based analytics. Requires Google OAuth 2.0 authentication with forms.responses.readonly scope. Useful for dashboards and reporting.

fields.Name: CompanyID
fields.Description: The Company Integration ID for Google Forms authentication

fields.Name: FormID
fields.Description: The Google Form ID

fields.Name: Filter
fields.Description: Filter expression for responses (e.g., 'timestamp > "2023-01-01T00:00:00Z"')

fields.Name: MaxResponses
fields.Description: Maximum responses to analyze (default 10000)

fields.Name: IncludeTopAnswers
fields.Description: Calculate most popular answers for each question (default true)

fields.Name: TopAnswersLimit
fields.Description: Number of top answers to return per question (default 10)

fields.Name: Statistics
fields.Description: Complete statistics object with all calculated metrics

fields.Name: TotalResponses
fields.Description: Total number of responses

fields.Name: CompletedResponses
fields.Description: Number of completed responses

fields.Name: PartialResponses
fields.Description: Number of partial/incomplete responses

fields.Name: CompletionRate
fields.Description: Percentage of responses that were completed

fields.Name: AverageResponseTime
fields.Description: Average time to complete in seconds (if available)

fields.Name: ResponsesByDate
fields.Description: Daily breakdown of response counts

fields.Name: DailyBreakdown
fields.Description: Array of daily statistics with date, count, completed, and partial counts

fields.Name: HourlyDistribution
fields.Description: Array showing response distribution by hour of day (0-23)

fields.Name: TopAnswers
fields.Description: Most popular answers by question ID

fields.Name: ResponseRate
fields.Description: Average responses per day

fields.Name: Export Google Forms Responses to CSV
fields.Description: Exports Google Form responses to CSV format for use in spreadsheets, data analysis tools, or archival. Requires Google OAuth 2.0 authentication with forms.responses.readonly scope. Supports custom delimiters and optional metadata columns.

fields.Name: CompanyID
fields.Description: The Company Integration ID for Google Forms authentication

fields.Name: FormID
fields.Description: The Google Form ID

fields.Name: Filter
fields.Description: Filter expression for responses to export (e.g., 'timestamp > "2023-01-01T00:00:00Z"')

fields.Name: IncludeMetadata
fields.Description: Include metadata columns (timestamp, respondent email, edit URL) - default true

fields.Name: Delimiter
fields.Description: CSV delimiter character (default: comma)

fields.Name: MaxResponses
fields.Description: Maximum responses to export (default 10000)

fields.Name: IncludeQuestionText
fields.Description: Use question text as column headers instead of question IDs (default true)

fields.Name: CSVData
fields.Description: CSV formatted string ready for export or storage

fields.Name: RowCount
fields.Description: Number of data rows in the CSV

fields.Name: Headers
fields.Description: Array of column headers

fields.Name: ColumnCount
fields.Description: Number of columns in the CSV

fields.Name: FileSize
fields.Description: Size of CSV data in bytes

fields.Name: Get Google Forms Details
fields.Description: Retrieves complete details of a Google Form including title, questions, settings, and metadata. Requires Google OAuth 2.0 authentication with forms.readonly scope. Use this to inspect or backup form configurations.

fields.Name: CompanyID
fields.Description: The Company Integration ID for Google Forms authentication

fields.Name: FormID
fields.Description: The Google Form ID to retrieve

fields.Name: Form
fields.Description: Complete form object with all configuration

fields.Name: Title
fields.Description: Form title

fields.Name: Description
fields.Description: Form description

fields.Name: Questions
fields.Description: Array of all form questions with types and properties

fields.Name: QuestionCount
fields.Description: Number of questions in the form

fields.Name: Settings
fields.Description: Form settings like accepting responses, quiz mode, email collection

fields.Name: QuizSettings
fields.Description: Quiz-specific settings if form is a quiz (grading options, feedback)

fields.Name: LinkedSheetID
fields.Description: Google Sheets ID if responses are linked to a spreadsheet

fields.Name: ResponderURI
fields.Description: Public URL where users can respond to the form

fields.Name: Summary
fields.Description: High-level summary with key metrics and information
